         Pudding

           or

 How to Collapse a Pit?


Consider the following situation in a team game:
 
|  bb     |
|  b      |
|  b a    |
|X   a XX |
|XXXXaXXXX| 1
|XXXXaXXXX| 2
|XXXX XXXX| 3
|XXXX XXXX| 4
|XX XXXXXX| 5
|XX XXXXXX| 6
|XXX XXX X| 7
|XXXX XX X| 8
|=========|

Player A drops brick a, causing lines 1..4 to disappear. When player B
drops brick b, lines 4 and 6 should disappear as well. However, in the
Archimedes version, if plr B is quick enough, brick b may be stuck in
the air, since not all of lines 1..4 may have disappeared at the time
of the drop of brick b. This is a bug.

Proper way to deal with this situation:

  1. When brick a is dropped, flag A as no brick, and if there are any
lines to be collapsed, set a flag (in LogPit) `COLLAPSING'.
  2. Every dt_COLLAPSE ms, collapse one line (starting from the top).
As soon as no further lines are collapsable, wait a further
dt_NEWBRICK before producing a new brick for player A, and unflagging
him `NOBRICK'.
  3. While a plr A is marked `NOBRICK', his WishList is not polled *):
there is no brick in the air. In particular, plr A cannot drop another
brick before the previous collapse has been fully handled.
  4. In the mean time, each time a line disappears _below_ brick b,
the latter is moved down as well. This does not interfere with b's
normal godown.
  5. If b lands (or is dropped) while the LogPit is still
`COLLAPSING', the time of the attempted drop is recording for the
purpose of scoring, and B is marked `NOBRICK: DELAYED_DROP'.
  6. When unmarking `NOBRICK', check if any plr is marked DELAYED_DROP,
and if so, execute the landing.


*) WishList::logkey is called, but ::poll is not.